Creevlea, otherwise Ballyruark or Carrig Patrick, but now commonly called Friarstown or Dromahare Abbey, is situated in the Barony of Dromahaire‚ near the town of that name, on the river Boonid, which falls into Lough Grill. It is an abbey in ruins.

A religious house was founded here for Franciscans of the Strict Observance, A.D. 1508, by Margaret O’Brien, daughter of Lord O'Brien and wife of Eugene Lord O’Ruark. She died in 1512 and was interred here. This building was never com- pleted, although it is said Lord O'Ruark gave twenty cows sor its erection.
